org.orgName: District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory

body.p: In the District Court holding terms at Seattle
In the matter of the application of No. 5930 Henry Carlton for Habeas Corpus

This cause coming on to be heard upon the Sheriffs return to the Writ of Habeas Corpus herein procuds by argument of counsel for the Territory as well as for Petitioner and the court not being sufficiently advised takes time and it is ordered by the Court that said petitioner give bond in the sum of one hundred dollars, for his appearance before the court on April 18th 1888 at 2 o'clock p.m. and to obey all orders of court until discharged and said Henry Carlton having deposited in the Registry of the Court the sum of One Hundred Dollars lawful money of the United States it is ordered by the court that he be discharged
Dated April 28th 1888 at 2 o'clock P.M. R.A. Jones, Judge
In the matter of the application of Henry Carlton for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
